race.comment: BLACK FROST (7) goes on top. He's only raced three times to date and been around the mark in all of them, stepping out to 1800m at Gundagai last start and closing well for third. This trip won't pose an issue, he draws well and can break through. DON'T LOOK AWAY (9) has had a few chances being a 19 start maiden but can be forgiven for the heavy track run last time at Ballarat, albeit not beaten far. The run two back reads well. SUPREME SAILING (11) has only raced twice to date, showing some improvement at Mornington last time out. Suspect she's crying out for more ground now which she gets. TILZATTACK (6) was better last time at Wangaratta and has each way claims off that. SCORPION BAY (4) perhaps next best.
